cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image inpainting, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a new normalization technique to improve the performance of neural networks for this task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of normalization on network training, which is related to machine learning and optimization, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as likely sub-categories. The proposed method involves dividing the image into regions based on the input mask, which is a form of segmentation, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia) as possible sub-categories.
